@startuml
title Viaverse AI Assistant / Support — Component Diagram

component "KMP / Next.js Client\nAI help entry\nsupport widget\nfeedback" as Client
component "API Gateway / BFF\nAI API\nSupport API" as BFF
component "AiAssistantController\nSupportController" as Controller
component "AI Use Cases\nAskAssistant\nSummarizeCase\nEscalateToSupport\nCollectFeedback" as UseCases
component "AI Policies\nprivacy guard\nprompt boundary\ntool allowlist\nhuman escalation" as Policies
component "Ports\nLlmPort\nKnowledgeRetrievalPort\nDomainContextPort\nSupportPort\nOutboxPort" as Ports
database "Knowledge Base\nFAQ\npolicies\nproduct docs\nsupport macros" as KB
component "LLM Adapter\nprovider switch\nbudget/timeout\ncontent filter" as LLM
component "support-service\ntickets\nagent workspace\ncase timeline" as Support
component "Domain Context Adapters\nidentity\njobs\npayments\nmedia\ntrust" as Domain
database "PostgreSQL\nai_session\nai_message\nsupport_ticket\nfeedback" as DB
queue "Kafka / Outbox\nAiAsked\nAiEscalated\nTicketResolved" as Kafka

Client --> BFF : HTTPS
BFF --> Controller : REST
Controller --> UseCases : command/query
UseCases --> Policies : validate
Policies --> Ports : ports
Ports --> KB : retrieve
Ports --> LLM : generate
Ports --> Support : ticket/escalate
Ports --> Domain : scoped context
Ports --> DB : persist
UseCases --> Kafka : events

note bottom
AI layer is an orchestration boundary, not a domain source-of-truth.
It reads scoped context and creates support/AI records;
business state changes stay in domain services.
end note
@enduml
